# =============================================================================
# File: /opt/ansible-k3s-cluster/README.kernel-deploy
# =============================================================================
# Purpose:
#   Document the process for deploying a newly built kernel from the builder
#   node to all cluster nodes using Ansible.
#
# Workflow:
#   1. Builder compiles kernel using distcc.
#   2. Builder produces:
#        - zImage
#        - dtbs
#        - modules
#   3. Ansible playbook copies kernel artifacts to each node.
#   4. Ansible installs modules under /lib/modules/<version>.
#   5. Ansible updates /boot on each node.
#   6. Ansible orchestrates a controlled reboot.
#
# Expected Kernel Output Paths:
#   /home/builder/linux-rpi-k3s/arch/arm/boot/zImage
#   /home/builder/linux-rpi-k3s/arch/arm/boot/dts/*.dtb
#   /home/builder/linux-rpi-k3s/modules/
#
# Deployment Playbook (to be created):
#   /opt/ansible-k3s-cluster/deploy-kernel.yml
#
# Notes:
#   - Kernel builds occur ONLY under the builder user.
#   - Kernel deployment occurs ONLY under the ansible user.
#   - This separation preserves auditability and operational boundaries.
# =============================================================================
